The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Mission centre in Srinagar
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Mission centre in Srinagar
                            
	Calcutta, Dec. 14: The 99th annual general meeting of Ramakrishna Mission was held at Belur Math last week.        
	Officials said the meeting was informed about the missions new centre in Srinagar and education projects.        
	Two courses  bachelor of physiotherapy and bachelor of optometry  were started at Ramakrishna Mission Seva Pratisthan in Calcutta. We also started a 13-bed nephrology unit, a cardiac cathertisation lab and a virtual museum of pathology in Lucknow, an official said.        
	The Blind Boys Academy of Narendrapur has started an audio book studio for publication of books on CDs.        
	During 2007-08, the official said, Ramakrishna Math and Mission undertook relief and rehabilitation programmes across the country involving Rs 3.97 crore and benefiting 18.39 lakh people. Over Rs 7 crore was spent on welfare work such as providing scholarships to poor students and aid to the old and destitute.                                                                                                                                                                         
